    "habitat": "Central and South America",
    "status": "Near threatened",
    "threats": "Climate change, habitat loss, hunting"
},
{
    "name": "Saola",
    "scientific_name": "Pseudoryx nghetinhensis",
    "habitat": "Vietnam and Laos",
    "status": "Critically endangered",
    "threats": "Climate change, habitat loss, hunting"
}]';

% Decode the JSON data
data = jsondecode(json_data);

% Filter for critically endangered species with climate change as a threat
isCriticallyEndangered = strcmp({data.status}, 'Critically endangered');
hasClimateChangeThreat = contains({data.threats}, 'Climate change');

% Combine both conditions
filteredData = data(isCriticallyEndangered & hasClimateChangeThreat);

% Convert to table for better visualization
critically_endangered_table = struct2table(filteredData);

% Display the table
disp(critically_endangered_table);
```

This script will filter the JSON data to include only those species that are classified as "Critically endangered" and have "Climate change" listed as one of their threats. The result will be displayed in a table format for easier visualization.
